      "content": "The new curriculum isn't just a different perspective; it actively rewrites established historical facts to fit a specific ideological narrative that ignores the contributions of white men and other dominant groups. This approach often relies on unproven theories like critical race theory to justify present-day political agendas rather than relying on verified evidence. By prioritizing these subjective interpretations over objective data, schools are effectively teaching students to distrust traditional historical records and accept a predetermined political worldview as truth.",
